reviewText: I am a little mad that this was not nominated for an Oscar. Robert L. Devaney put a modern spin on the classic cinderella story. I laughed, I cried, I was on an emotional rollercoaster. I was captivated by an enthralling performance by the Sine Function and the chemistry he had with his co-star Square Root. I was on the edge of my seat the entire movie especially when they revealed the twist at the end. It is a crime against hollywood and cinema as a whole to not have see this movie, I just wished my local IMAX would screen it.
I was disappointed. The lectures were a little dry. I thought the dvd had more videos of actual fractals, not just a lecture about them.
